title: thirdparty intermediaries
extract: According to the Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD), third-party intermediaries (third parties) are people who help connect two or more trading partners, generally as “a conduit for goods or services offered by a supplier to a consumer.”Aug 18, 2017
